task.summary: Default task
- Initial Commit, moved project to Git
- Second Commit to git - Added some new class headers and implementation
- Fixed a bug with default constructors/destructors

- Created a simple, efficient header file describing how the puzzle shall be solved. Each 3x3 grid will be checked for a 1-9 grid. If it fails, we check each of the 9 numbers within the grid in order to see if any of them fail both the row and column test. Then we find a solution to recommend, and return an object with the answer.
- Added a simple vector list to organize values, for 3x3 grid checking before going into full loop
- Added a simple vector list to organize values, for 3x3 grid checking before going into full loop

- Used a typedef to define a pair type (int x, int y) - Used a typdef to define a vector of pairs - Created a more smooth checking function (for numbers 1-9) utilizing some distribution of responsibilities between functions. - Documented and added comments for future reference - Learned vector insertion and iteration techniques
- Finished initial version of GridChecking
- Added some more useful features - Debugged, build is now in a working state - Cleaned up some type mismatches, fixed some more errors elsewhere within code - Added some more documentation
- Created a simple and effective constructor for GridCheck class instantiation.
- Added in File I/O
- Fixed loop bug
- Added stuff to main - Discovered error with pointer being passed into GridCheck object creation
- Fixed logical errors
- Fixed a logical error regarding one of the checking functions - Removed else statement in order to allow function to fully execute
-- Changed functions around quite fully and definitely -- Adding ErrorObjects is now encapsulated within the checkNum function, with a bool value returned
-- Added preliminary threading support
-- Beta Version Testing now
- Project Almost complete! Just need to fix possible answer recommendation (issue arises on 5th unit test)
- Working on Answer solutions
-- Need to deal with segmentation fault in check method, after you find a version. Could be something with the readIn 9x9 grid we are passing a pointer in as
- Some more testing done, still haven't discovered error quite yet
- Unstable commit before fix
- Almost finished
- Working Version! Just need to clean up and add tweaks
- Little more code cleanup
- Adding output throughout execution, informing the user of what is happening at each essential step
